People of Qwaqwa in the Free State are threatening another shutdown despite Water and Sanitation Minister Lindiwe Sisulu's intervention last week. QWAQWA - People of Qwaqwa in the Free State are threatening another shutdown despite Water and Sanitation Minister Lindiwe Sisulu's intervention last week. The minister promised to bring 5,000 tanks to the area to try and help with the water situation. READ: 5,000 water tanks, R220m allocated for QwaQwa water relief One community leader was reportedly arrested on Monday morning for incitement to public violence. Shutdown leader Bigboy Mazibuko said the community members do not want rainwater harvesting tanks. READ: Taps are dry in Qwaqwa Another community member said the residents of QwaQwa have not had water for ten years and the harvesting tanks are insufficient for water access.